"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529282","Department of Health","false","2016-07-04","<p>I am currently planning to visit the West Cumberland Hospital in the coming months.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-07-04T15:38:55.283Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529282/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529282/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529282/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-28","West Cumberland Hospital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he next plans to visit West Cumberland Hospital in an official capacity.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","41367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529283","Department of Health","false","2016-07-04","<p>The Secretary of State for Health and his Ministerial team have not undertaken any visits in an official capacity to the West Cumberland Hospital in the last four years.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-07-04T15:39:38.387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529283/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529283/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529283/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-28","West Cumberland Hospital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times he has visited West Cumberland Hospital in an official capacity in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","41368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529284","Home Office","false","2016-07-06","<p>Since October 2012, the provision of police air support has been the responsibility of the National Police Air Service (NPAS), a police-led operational initiative designed to deliver a cost effective and efficient service to forces in England and Wales. It is the responsibility of the NPAS Strategic Board, comprising police and crime commissioners and chief constables, to make decisions on the deployment of resources to meet local policing and crime priorities.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-07-06T10:07:25.613Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529284/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529284/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529284/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-28","Police: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effect of the potential closure of the Lancashire Police helicopter base on the safety of the local Fylde community.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","41342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529285","Home Office","false","2016-07-05","<p>The 2016-17 budget for the Gangmasters Licensing Authority has been published on page 80 of the Main Supply Estimates 2016-17, which is available to the public. The GLA will receive increased funding to reflect its changing and broader functions and we remain committed to resourcing the GLA to ensure it can deliver on its purpose of protecting vulnerable and exploited workers.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-07-05T16:42:37.693Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529285/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529285/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529285/answer","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529285/answer/previousversion/5699","Biography information for Karen Bradley","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-28","Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she plans to announce the budget for the new Gangmasters and Labour Abuse Authority; and whether that budget will be expanded in comparison to that of the Gangmasters Licensing Authority to reflect the wider remit and powers of the new body.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","41352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529286","Home Office","false","2016-06-30","<p>The table below shows the number of potential victims of human trafficking or modern slavery who were referred to the National Referral Mechanism (NRM) in the UK between 2011 and 2015.</p><p>The NRM is the UK’s identification and support mechanism for potential victims of modern slavery.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of potential victims</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>946</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1,186</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>1,746</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2,340</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>3,266</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>A breakdown of referrals is available from published NRM statistics on the National Crime Agency website and can be found here: www.nationalcrimeagency.gov.uk/publications/national-referral-mechanism-statistics</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-30T14:45:33.87Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529286/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/529286/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-28","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many cases of slavery have been reported in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","41383"
