"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528913","Department of Health","false","2016-06-30","<p>NHS England advises that there is not one single organisation accountable for the operation of the National Health Service in Mid Sussex, West Sussex or Brighton. Instead, each of the NHS organisations in these areas is accountable for the different operational aspects of the provision of NHS services.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England further advises that it commissions a comprehensive health service for patients in this area along with the Coastal West Sussex Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG); Crawley CCG; Horsham and Mid Sussex CCG; and Brighton and Hove CCG.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-30T15:57:05.873Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528913/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528913/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-27","Health Services: Sussex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what local organisation is accountable for the operation of the NHS in (a) Mid Sussex, (b) West Sussex and (c) Brighton.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","41261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528914","Department of Health","false","2016-07-05","<p>Information on gum disease is collected through snap shot surveys at 10 year intervals. Separate surveys are carried out for adults and children and the data in each is not comparable.</p><p> </p><p>The Health and Social Care Information Centre are able to provide data from the Adult Dental Health Survey 2009 and the Child Dental Health Survey 2013; these are available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.hscic.gov.uk/pubs/dentalsurveyfullreport09" target="_blank">http://www.hscic.gov.uk/pubs/dentalsurveyfullreport09</a></p><p> </p><p>and</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.hscic.gov.uk/catalogue/PUB17137" target="_blank">www.hscic.gov.uk/catalogue/PUB17137</a></p><p> </p><p>respectively.</p><p>The surveys cover England, Wales and Northern Ireland; they do not cover Scotland so United Kingdom figures are not available.</p><p> </p><p>These surveys provide numbers of adults (those aged 16 years and over) and children aged 15 years surveyed who exhibited symptoms of periodontal (gum) disease. The surveys showed that 108 adults out of a sample size of 6,430 and 40 children out of a sample size of 2,418 showed signs of gum disease.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-07-05T10:56:09.103Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528914/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528914/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-27","Dental Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of people in the UK who had gum disease in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","41312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528915","Department of Health","false","2016-07-05","<p>All clinically necessary dental treatment is available on the National Health Service and it is for a clinician to determine the best treatment option for a patient.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-07-05T10:23:14.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528915/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528915/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-27","Dental Health: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will make laser treatment for chronic gum disease available on the NHS.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","41313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528916","Department of Health","false","2016-07-05","<p>The number of people of each gender over the age of 50 who have been in drug or alcohol treatment for the last five years can be accessed in the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.ndtms.net/Publications/AnnualReports.aspx" target="_blank">https://www.ndtms.net/Publications/AnnualReports.aspx</a></p><p> </p><p><em>Source:</em> National Drug Treatment Monitoring System</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-07-05T15:11:19.05Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528916/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528916/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-27","Alcoholic Drinks and Drugs: Misuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people of each gender over the age of 50 have been treated for (a) drug and (b) alcohol addiction in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","41314"
