"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528926","Home Office","false","2016-07-11","<p>The Home Office is committed to treating all those who seek asylum with dignity and respect, including those whose fears may be based on sexual violence or gender related persecution.</p><p>All general Immigration Officers receive training in Modern Slavery issues and those based at dedicated Asylum Intake Unit where claims may be first registered also receive training in sexual violence awareness. However, all asylum claims are dealt with by specially trained caseworkers rather than Immigration Officers.</p><p>The current training and support available for asylum caseworkers includes a UNHCR endorsed Foundation Training Programme, which covers all aspects of the asylum interview and decision making process, including dealing sensitively with vulnerable claimants.</p><p>Furthermore we have also worked closely with stakeholders, such as, the Refugee Council, to develop a dedicated referral process, so that women are formally referred to special counselling services where they disclose issues relating to sexual violence as part of their asylum claim.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-07-11T16:21:47.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528926/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528926/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528926/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-27","Immigration Officers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what training her Department provides to immigration officers on handling asylum cases in which a claimant has been raped or sexually abused.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","41280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528927","Home Office","false","2016-07-06","<p>The Department's purchasing policies support the Government’s commitment to do all it can to ensure UK suppliers can compete effectively for public sector contracts, in line with our current international obligations and guidance issued by the Crown Commercial Service.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-07-06T13:18:30.08Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528927/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528927/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528927/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-27","Home Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will take steps to ensure that her Department's purchasing policies support British (a) industry and (b) agriculture.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","41272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528928","House of Commons Commission","false","2016-07-04","<p>The House of Commons procurement policies operate within the parameters set out by the UK Public Contracts Regulations 2015.</p><p>The House has a Sustainable Purchasing Policy which, amongst other things, requires contracts that are particularly suitable for SMEs to be highlighted as so being, contracts to be divided into lots and processes to be as simple and proportionate as possible to encourage SMEs to participate in our competitions. Further, the policy requires contracts that are suitable for Social Enterprises to be identified at an early stage and that market engaged to ensure their participation.</p><p>More generally, the House supports British industry and agriculture by:</p><ul><li>Purchasing our goods and services in a way that maximises the ability of SMEs, Social Enterprises and organisations with less bargaining power to win our contracts;</li><li>Conducting open and competitive tender processes that are accessible to all British suppliers whether small, medium or large;</li><li>Advertising our contracts on the UK Government procurement website Contracts Finder and the House’s own electronic procurement portal to ensure that there is maximum visibility of our contractual opportunities;</li><li>Writing specifications of requirements that take into account domestic social, economic and environmental requirements.</li></ul>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2016-07-04T15:58:42.793Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528928/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528928/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528928/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2016-06-27","House of Commons: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Rt. hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington representing the House of Commons Commission, if he will take steps to ensure that the House of Commons Commission's purchasing policies support British (a) industry and (b) agriculture.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","41273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528929","Department for International Development","false","2016-07-04","<p>The Department's purchasing policies support the Government’s commitment to do all it can to ensure UK suppliers can compete effectively for public sector contracts, in line with our current international obligations and guidance issued by the Crown Commercial Service.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-07-04T15:41:58.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528929/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528929/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528929/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-06-27","Department for International Development: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will take steps to ensure that her Department's purchasing policies support British (a) industry and (b) agriculture.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","41274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528930","Department for International Development","false","2016-07-04","<p>HM Treasury will commission 5-year Official Development Assistance spending plans from all departments. The departmental plans are expected to be finalised by the end of the calendar year.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-07-04T15:42:44.09Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528930/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528930/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528930/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-06-27","Development Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 13 June 2016 to Question 39301, whether there is a timetable in place for other departments to establish and implement their plans to monitor official development assistance spending.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","41291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528931","Department for International Development","false","2016-07-04","<p>All departments or funds spending official development assistance (ODA) are responsible for ensuring they provide accurate and timely information on their ODA to the Department for International Development (DFID). DFID provides on-going support on data collection, and collates the information for in-year monitoring of ODA and the final reporting of UK ODA statistics.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-07-04T15:44:57.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528931/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528931/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528931/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-06-27","Development Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 13 June 2016 to Question 39301, what systems are in place for departments and funds spending official development assistance (ODA) to provide accurate and timely information on their ODA spending to her Department.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","41292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528932","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-30","<p>We are working with a range of organisations, including Rights of Women, the Law Society, Resolution, and the Legal Aid Practitioners Group.</p><p> </p><p>With the guidance of these organisations, and through their associated networks, we have sought to target those with direct experience of how the regulations operate in practice - for victims and practitioners – as we think this is the best way to inform how those regulations may be improved. We have also begun work with the Home Office, as the lead department on domestic violence policy, to better understand the wider context of domestic violence.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2016-06-30T15:15:12.59Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528932/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528932/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528932/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-27","Legal Aid Scheme: Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 27 June 2016 to Question 40498, on domestic violence: legal aid scheme, which domestic violence support groups, legal representative bodies and colleagues across Government the Department is working with; and on what basis the decision was made to work with those organisations and not others.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","41295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528933","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-07-05","<p>The Ministry of Justice complies with all public procurement policy notes, published at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/procurement-policy-notes" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/procurement-policy-notes</a>. These include measures to support both British industry and British agriculture.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-07-05T14:23:55.8Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528933/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528933/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-27","Ministry of Justice: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will take steps to ensure that his Department's purchasing policies support British (a) industry and (b) agriculture.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","41275"
